Angular component lifecycle hooks 

There are 8 lifecycle hooks in angular 

1. ngOnIt()
2. ngOnChanges()
3. ngDoCheck()
4. ngAfterContentInit()
5. ngAfterContentChecked()
6. ng ngAfterViewInit()
7. ngAfterDoChecked()
8. ngOnDestroy()



By default we have ngOnIt 

 Whichever lifecycle hooks we want to use
    1. import it in the class 
    2. Extend the implements interface 
    3. Implement the method  

 We can have any number of lifecycle hooks implemented 


